lass=\"body\">\n              <b>Power bill</b> for <em>RACK-01</em> ran <b>13% over forecast</b>. Cooling fans on duty cycle since 22:00.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"impact neg\">−$8.40<small>cost overrun</small></div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"event info\">\n            <div class=\"ts\">09:22 PM<br>Day 11</div>\n            <div class=\"ico\">⌖</div>\n            <div class=\"body\">\n              New lead <b>Mira Sato @ glassmap</b> requested a quote for a GPU pod in Tokyo. Budget: $1.2k/mo. 48h response window.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"impact pos\">prospect<small>$1,200 ARR</small></div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"event\">\n            <div class=\"ts\">07:01 PM<br>Day 11</div>\n            <div class=\"ico\">$</div>\n            <div class=\"body\">\n              <b>Stripe payout</b> received. Karen Holloway · $19.00 · invoice <em>INV-0019</em>.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"impact pos\">+$19.00</div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"event info\">\n            <div class=\"ts\">05:44 PM<br>Day 11</div>\n            <div class=\"ico\">◉</div>\n            <div class=\"body\">\n              Forum post <b>\"Anyone tried SyncNode?\"</b> on /r/budgethosting — 14 upvotes, 6 comments. Sentiment: <em>cautiously curious</em>.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"impact pos\">+2 leads</div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"event warn\">\n            <div class=\"ts\">02:10 PM<br>Day 11</div>\n            <div class=\"ico\">⚠</div>\n            <div class=\"body\">\n              <b>Anon @ burner</b> asked if you log egress. Replying poorly = lose a paying customer. Replying yes = a Karen Holloway forum thread.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"impact neg\">decision<small>P2 open</small></div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n      </section>\n\n      <!-- Right column: rack + mood -->\n      <div class=\"side-stack\">\n        <section class=